  "description": "Johan Thorsten Israel Bengtsson (1893-10-24) was a bank director from Gothenburg, Sweden. He was born in Reftele, Jönköping County as the eldest child of agronomist Anders B. Bengtsson and Helène Samuelsson. He married Asta Lundgren in 1921 and they had a son named Bertil in 1926. Bengtsson had a high school diploma (1911), a law degree (1916), and a Bachelor of Philosophy (1918). He traveled to England in 1924-1925 and to the USA in 1932 and 1933. He worked at Försäkr. A-B Nornan from 1918-1929, Brand- and Livförsäkr. A-B Svea from 1929-1932, and A-B Gbgs Bank from 1934-1939. He served as a trustee, vice director, deputy managing director, and managing director in various organizations and was the chairman of the board of directors for the association De fatt. vänner. Bengtsson wrote several articles in economics for Statsvet:skapl. Tidskr., Nord. Försäkr:tidskr., and others."
